Jeff Wicks, News24(ANCWL) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The ANC Women&rsquo;s League on Wednesday called for a &ldquo;full investigation&rdquo; into state capture that should include white monopoly capital. The ANCWL had noted the release of the &ldquo;State of Capture&rdquo; report and would comment once it had studied it, secretary general Meokgo Matuba said in a statement.&nbsp;&ldquo;We hold a firm view that there is a need for a full investigation on state capture. Any investigation which excludes white monopoly capital is an advancement of white supremacy and serves a racial political agenda that hinders the building of a non-racial society,&rdquo; Matuba said.She appealed to the ANC-led government to make resources available to the public protector&rsquo;s office to start a full investigation immediately.She said the ANCWL had confidence in the democratically-elected ANC leadership and the ANC-led government under President Jacob Zuma.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.